{
  "texts": [
    "For any possibility frames F and G, the following are equivalent:1. there is a strict strong embedding from F into G; 2.",
    "F is isomorphic to a selective subframe of G.In addition, for any possibility frames F and G, the following are equivalent: 3. there is a p-morphism that is a strong embedding from F to G; 4.",
    "F is isomorphic to a generated subframe of G.Proof.",
    "From 1 to 2, where h is the strict strong embedding of F into G, we first claim that the subframeG ′ of G with domain h[S F] is a selective subframe of G. Suppose x G ∈ h[S F] and y G ⊑ G x G. Thus, x G = h(x F) for some x F ∈ F. Then since y G ⊑ G h(x F) and h is a strict possibility morphism, by ⊑-back there is a y F ∈ F such that h(y F) ⊑ G y G. Then taking z G = h(y F), we have z G ∈ h[S F] and z G ⊑ G y G, so G ′ satisfies part 4 of Definition 5.52.",
    "Next, suppose x G = h(x F)R G i y G. Then by R-back, there is a y F ∈ F such x F R F i y F and h(y F) ≬ G y G. By R-forth, x F R F i y F implies h(x F)R G i h(y F)."
  ]
}